text.__SUMMARY__: Aspergillus fumisynnematus is a species of fungus in the genus Aspergillus. It is from the Fumigati section. The species was first described in 1993. It has been reported to produce neosartorin, pyripyropens, and fumimycin.
text.Growth and morphology:
A. fumisynnematus has been cultivated on both Czapek yeast extract agar (CYA) plates and Malt Extract Agar Oxoid® (MEAOX) plates. The growth morphology of the colonies can be seen in the pictures below.
